(7, 'Paediatric Surgery', 'upload/surgery/Website-Child-200x300.jpg', 'Pediatric Surgery is the field of surgery for the treatment of conditions that can be surgically corrected in a baby, child or adolescent. This can vary depending on the type of procedure, where the purpose is to surgically correct a congenital condition, disease, traumatic injury or other disorders'),
(8, 'Spinal Surgery', 'upload/surgery/spinal.jpg', 'Spinal Surgery is a subspecialty of Orthopaedic Surgery which involves diagnosis and surgical intervention of conditions of the spine.\r\nThe purpose of spinal surgery is to improve pain, function and quality of life.  The objective is to obtain consistently safe with excellent surgical outcomes. Surg'),
(9, 'Urology', 'upload/surgery/uro.jpg', 'Urology surgery is primarily for the treatment of obstructions, dysfunction, malignancies and inflammatory diseases of the colon, urogenital and gynecological organs. As well as management of many non-surgical problems, such as urinary infections, urologists deal with diseases, trauma and congenital'),
(10, 'Vascular surgery', 'upload/surgery/vasc.jpg', 'Vascular surgery is the division of medicine which specialises in treating blood vessels of the body, with the exception of the vessels of the heart. A vascular surgeon is trained in the diagnosis and management of diseases affecting the vascular system. They may work to restore blood flow to an are'),
(11, 'Bariatric Surgery (Weight Loss Surgery)', 'upload/surgery/bariatric-surgery.jpg', 'Bariatric (Weight Loss) Surgery assists in weight loss and maybe recommended as a last resort when diet, exercise and medication have not been successful and if obesity related conditions such as heart disease, asthma, high blood pressure, sleep apnoea and type II diabetes have worsened, amongst oth'),
