(13, 'Discectomy ', 'upload/surgery/discectomy.jpg', 'Discectomy is the surgical removal of part or all of a herniated or bulging intervertebral disc that presses against a nerve root or the spinal cord itself and causes pain and other symptoms. The aim of surgery is to achieve decompression by removing bone or soft tissue compressing the contents of t'),
(14, 'Arthroscopy', 'upload/surgery/14.jpg', 'Arthroscopy is a surgical procedure by which the internal structure of a joint is examined for diagnosis and/or treatment using a tube-like viewing instrument called an arthroscope. Arthroscopy was popularized in the 1960s with the advent of fiberoptic technologies and is now commonplace throughout '),
